00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
In 1905, the British government announced the Partition of Bengal.

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:09,000
Under the leadership of Viceroy Lord Curzon, Bengal was divided citing 'administrative convenience.'

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,000
But Indians saw it as an attempt to divide and rule — to split Hindus and Muslims.

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:17,000
The Swadeshi Movement emerged — boycotting British goods and promoting unity.

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:21,000
The Partition was eventually annulled in 1911, but it had already ignited a nationalist fire.
